Rating: 0
Winner for sure. It's really not that tedious to make. I made it in two dutch ovens which really made it easy. I also added some mushrooms and a little cayenne pepper since I like a little heat. I will say that the stew base was a bit thin and not as bold as I wanted right when I pulled it from the oven. So, instead of tossing the braised veggies, I picked out most of them, tossed them in the blender with a little stew juice and pureed them then returned the whole thing back into the stew (make sure to squeeze the garlic out of it's paper shells back into the stew as well). Made a huge difference. Much bolder flavors and also acted as perfect thickener. I'm gluten free so I didn't want to dredge the meat in flour. No need, this trick works and adds much flavor to the stew. People LOVED it. Will be making again for sure. If you're trying to save a couple $ you can go with less meat, the 5lbs is a lot of meat.

