Rating: 3
This recipe has one major error - the use of balsamic vinegar. Quality and taste (sweetness/thickness) of balsamic varies GREATLY. Some is suitable as an ice cream topping others are much lighter. I use high quality, and used only 1/4 cup and my son who is not a picky eater complained it was too sweet. I used Cabernet for the wine. So you really need to consider your particular type of balsamic combined with how dry the wine you are using is. In general I think this recipe would be better with very little or no balsamic (maybe a couple tablespoons of good quality, or max 1/4 cup of low quality/weak balsamic) Can't believe this go 4 stars with this flaw.

