Rating: 3
I'm embarking on a kitchen renovation next week and decided to have a cook-a-thon for food that can accomodate my soon to be relationship with a microwave. Since I had already packed my recipe for beef stew, like you, I went to my next source ... I wouldn't call this "traditional beef stew" and was surprised at how similar the recipe is to my favorite braised short ribs. I decided to give it a try to see if the taste was similar without all of the fat and it turned out quite well. I made it short-rib style and browned the beef (cubed tri-tip), remove from the dutch oven, saute 2/3 cups each of medium diced onion, carrots and celery for 6 - 8 minutes, add 1 tbs. chopped thyme, 1-1/2 cups beef broth and 1-1/2 cups dry red wine. No water and no tomato paste. After 2-3/4 hours in a 325 degree oven (I've also made in a slow cooker), remove the beef, add 1 tbsp. balsamic vinegar to the sauce (don't pitch the vegetables!), season, pour over the beef and sprinkle with parsley. I serve with mashed potatoes or pasta. 3 forks as again, not a traditional "stew", but the flavors are fab. If you want, try it with the short ribs!

