Love this recipe. Made it last year too. Reheats beautifully but does not freeze well. I do not strain and discard the solids as recommended because the onion, garlic, celery and carrots add a hearty texture to the stew that my husband loves. Instead of just halving the garlic head, I peel each clove, cut it in half and throw it in. That way, the only thing I remove at the end is the bay leaves and sprigs of thyme.

