Rating: 3
Past Review Dos and Don'ts: Do: use all the vinegar. It seems harsher right out of the oven but mellows out after a day. Don't: coat the beef with flour before browning. It just makes an impenetrable crust on the bottom of the pan, preventing proper browning. Do: puree the strained veggie bits. It adds tons of flavor and body to the dish.

