Rating: 4
With the right tweaks, this recipe is absolutely amazing. I made this on the stovetop with no problem, and followed a number of previous recommendations: 1. cubed beef chuck in 1", not 2" pieces 2. lightly dusted beef with flour before browning 3. did not discard first round of vegetables, but rather pureed them and added at the end to both thicken and flavor the stew 4. used 6 cups of beef stock and no water 5. added 1lb of sliced white mushrooms. I also added about 2 tbl of pepper in the beginning; would probably be too much for many people, but you'll absolutely need more than the recipe calls for. I'll certainly be making this again come winter!

