Wow, what a great stew. I cant believe anybody commented on it being labor-intensive. Most of it is just the stew sitting on the stovetop or in the oven. And the prepping of the vegetables, what can you say? Those veggies arent going to cut themselves. Anyway, I did this in between house painting . . . Paint one coat; while its drying, chop some vegetables; while stew is cooking, paint another coat; while paint is drying, chop some more vegetables . . . Anyway, I cut meat to 2 lb (nice amount) and dredged 1/2 of it through 3T flour. Not sure if this helped much. Next time Im going to try it w/o the flour. Then I pureed first set of vegetables, but next time I might not even do this. I might just leave them in. (They are delicious; no need to dig them out and toss them.) I also added mushrooms and parsnips and cut potatoes to 2 lb. Next time I might cut potatoes to 1.5 lb. Also, I used lean chuck stew meat, but this would be a great recipe to try out different meats, especially cheap cuts. Id probably stay away from fattier cuts unless you want to skim grease off top before serving.

