Rating: 4
I modified this recipe to utilize my crockpot. Essentially, I followed the recipe to the letter, but didn't braise the meat. I dredged the meat chunks in a seasoned flour mixture of salt and pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika (indian store). I just seared it for a few minutes, making sure to turn and sear all sides. I set the meat aside, and continued with the recipe. I then poured all the contents into the crockpot with meat, set it to low, and let it cook for about 11 hours. Unreal!!! This is soooo good! Yes, serve with some good crusty bread, and might I add, a good beer or a dry red wine. It's a very complex and rich stew...lots of depth. Wow it's good!

