Wow! Truly exceptional. Although the process can take a while, I found it very simple, especially if you're familiar with the time frames of making stews. Dusted the meat with flour, and only used about 3 pounds of beef because that was all I had. As a matter of fact, I think a dryness issue with some other reviewers lies in the amount of juices per meat and veggies. 2.5 lbs. of beef was perfect. Also, I only braised it for 1 hr and 45 minutes, and then I let it simmer on the stove top for an additional 30 minutes, adding some frozen peas, corn and 1 3/4 chopped potatoes. I used the remaining 1/4 of the potato to grate into the stew, making it an absolutely PERFECT texture. I made this tonight for my sick room mates and they rave about this recipe. Definitely, definitely a keeper. It's so easy to diversify it, too!

