Rating: 4
The carrots are indeed added to the recipe in 2 places. I did not add any water. Instead of 3 cups water and 3 cups broth, I chose to add 6 cups of broth. (Or, if you like, 3 cups water and 3 cups canned beef broth concentrate.) Also, after the initial stewing and after I had taken out all the meat, I removed the bay leaves and any garlic peel. I then took the leftover vegetable and pureed them in blender and added them back to the stew as a thickening agent.

Rating: 4
To "A cook from Stillwater, MN", you are, in fact, supposed to use carrots in both places of the recipe. In the first part, the carrots add flavor to the broth. In the second part, the carrots are added to the stew with the potatoes. Hope that helps for the future. As for my review- this came out very well! It was a great recipe to make on my day off and resulted in a savory stew that earned the boyfriend's stamp of approval. Will definitely make again.

