this was by far the best stew i've ever had. i'm not even the biggest fan of stew, but this was so yummy!! i usually find the flavors in stew to be a bit muddled, but this had such bright flavors. you CANNOT use the temp printed though or your meat will probably end up tough (this happened to me with so many stew/braise recipes from this site--finally i realized that it needs a LOW SIMMER max--which i did and my meat was sooooooo tender--about 250 for me.) modifications, in case they affected the outcome (apart from the fact that i quartered the recipe, since my family is 2 not 12): i left out celery (don't like it & am on a budget), made mashed potatoes and so did not add potatoes in the last step--added green beans instead about 15 mins before the end. ALSO because there was no potato starch to thicken the stew i added a few TBS of arrowroot.

