This was delicious and beautiful. It could hold its own in a nice restaurant or for company. I made this in my slow cooker that has a removable insert which permits stovetop browning of ingredients, so it was simple to make. I cooked it for 7 hours on "low" followed by 1 hour on "high." Did not remove or puree the vegetables, just left them in, and added the cooked potatoes at the end (a pound and a half of Russian fingerlings, cut up). I cooked the carrots with the original ingredients, as well as a turnip. I used 2-1/2 lbs. of beef (not 5 pounds), 4 carrots, no celery but some ground celery seed for the flavor, one minced garlic clove only, and half the amounts of liquid that the recipe calls for, as the overall quantities the recipe calls for would have produced too much for us. I can't imagine it could have been any better. Regarding reviewers who complained about dryness, I wonder if they cooked the stew using a pot with a lid that didn't fit tightly enough.

