The flavor for this recipe makes it a 4-forker. The process and quantities listed need adjustment so I only gave it three forks as written. The flavor is great. I cooked as suggested and pulled the stew out of the oven after 2.5 hours very very dry. I added 5 cups of beef broth in order to cook the veggies. If I did it again, I would use 1.5 to 2 bottles of wine for 5 pounds of meat and adjust with additional broth after the meat has cooked. I did not bother to strain the vegetables, I just picked out the garlic halves ( squeezed out any remaining garlic cloves into the pot) and removed the carrots that cook with the meat. I adjusted liquid levels and added fresh carrots and potatoes. I think this process is easier and achieves a more complex broth than the way it i written. Definitely a make again.

