Rating: 4
This is an excellent recipe, but I made it on top of the stove to save time and simplified it a little. I only browned the beef--didn't use carrots, onions etc. at beginning. Instead, I put whole onion and whole garlic clove in the water while beef boiling, which I removed at the end. I used about 2.5lb beef, 4c water, 3tbsp balsamic, and 1c wine. I simmered covered on low for one hour, then uncovered and put in 4 carrots chopped into 2 inch pieces and let it simmer uncovered for 20 minutes. I then added 5 coarsely chopped russet potatoes and simmered uncovered for another 40 minutes. 2 hours total cooking time, and it was the perfect consistency and had plenty of flavor.

Rating: 4
Great recipe. I modified it slightly based on others' reviews. I dusted the meat with flour before browning, and when I strained all the veggies from the stew sauce, I cooked potatoes and mushrooms in the sauce alone. Then when they were done, I put the meat back in. Didn't use additional carrots, but threw in some pearl onions as I had them on hand. I ended up cooking this in the oven for about an hour, but after I saw it wasn't cooking fast enough I used the stovetop for the rest of the braising. If I have enough time next time, I'll use the oven. Overall the stew was fantastic, and the smell in the kitchen from this stew was phenomenal. I've saved this recipe to my tastebook (www.tastebook.com) and I'll definitely make this again. Its a great cold weather meal.

Rating: 4
Excellent flavor--the tomato paste and balsamic make the stew. I made it on top of the stove instead of the oven, and did not use the vegetables in the beginning. I halved the recipe because I only had 2.5lb of beef. I just browned the beef, added 4c water, 1c wine, 3 Tbsp. balsamic, one whole onion unchopped, and a garlic clove. I simmered it on low for one hour covered, then uncovered it, added the carrots, and 20 minutes after that added 5 coarsley chopped russet potatoes, cooking for a total of 2 hours. Turned out the perfect consistency, and a little faster and easier than the original recipe.

