Rating: 4
After enjoying this prepared by friends, I finally attempted it and took into account some comments by others. Accordingly, I did obtain additional liquid from the braising veggies by pressing them with the back of a spoon, and I added a little more beef broth. So I did have enough liquid for the final potato and carrot stage. However, I had to cook it so much longer (total of 2 hours) in the oven because the potatos and carrots weren't cooking through. I suspect that the liquid cools far too much during that 10 minute "resting time" (and the pot cools somewhat too) for the 40 minutes back in the oven to be sufficient. Next time I will try simemring on the stove to quickly return it to a proper temperature before returning it to the oven. I may also try the suggestion by others to cook those potatos and carrots in the braised liquid without the cooked beef, then returning beef to the stew later. I hesitate to cook the potatos/carrots separately as you need the starch from them to naturally thicken the stew. Anyway, I am not deterred - I will definitely be making this again because it's so good!

