Rating: 4
I'm giving this 4 stars based on family consensus. Frigid weather this year in New Jersey has me turning to comfort foods and the economy has me minding my budget so I've been in search of a good beef stew recipe. I previously tried the Beef Bourguinon recipe from this site, but the kids gave it a thumbs down. I tried this recipe armed with that experience plus the wise counsel of previous reviewers. So.... I floured the beef before browning, used a little more red wine and beef broth than the recipe called for, cooked the carrots and potatoes w/o the already tender beef and re-introduced the beef plus some pearl onions and frozen peas towards the very end of cooking. Result: Perfection and a happy family. I served the stew over egg noodles, but they almost seemed extraneous. Still, the kids enjoyed the noodles. Since this recipe is not that dissimilar from the Beef Borguinon recipe, I have to chalk the success up to the addition of the balsamic and tomato paste. Those additions really add a whole new level of flavor. Finally, it is essential to begin this recipe the DAY BEFORE you plan to serve it. First, so that you don't feel rushed trying to get this meal on the table and second to allow the flavors develop. With temps still near zero here, I am really looking forward to making this recipe again!

Rating: 3
I've made this recipe twice now and the taste is great, but I have one issue - appearance. After 2-1/2 hours braising, the beef is so tender that when you enter the vegetable cooking step (even though I use a very large kettle), the stirring of the carrots and potatoes causes most all of the beef pieces to shred into strands of beef. This doesn't change the flavor, but it makes for an unappetizing appearance. Perhaps one could cook the vegetables only in the braising liquid, not adding back the beef until they are done. Aside from this, the receipe is also a lot of trouble, though not difficult. For taste, ease of prep and appearance, I think I much prefer Mahogany Beef Stew, a great recipe on this site.

