My pot is currently on the last step of the recipe (simmer 40 min.), so I can't report on the finished dish, but I do have a comment for people who are having trouble getting enough cooking liquid to accommodate the carrots and potatoes. After removing the solids and incorporating the carrots and potatoes, I too found that there wasn't enough liquid in the pot to cover the new additions. I went back to the colander of "solids" and pressed the mixture with the back of a spoon. This yielded perhaps as much as 2 cups of additional liquid, which was enough to "submerge" the carrots and potatoes appropriately. I'll let the stew rest for a day or two as recommended by other reviewers and then report back.

