Yes! Wonderful flavor to this stew. I skipped the wine, added Braggs Amino Acids for a little flavor, and didn't need to salt it (though I did a smidge). I also skipped the onion because I was out (I had maybe 1/4 cup minced in the fridge that I threw in.) I used a "charcoal steak" for the meat, a cheap cut they sell in my area that is roast meat cut thin. Perfect! So tender. I also only used 3 lb of meat - since that's what I had. Plenty. I made homemade vegetable stock from veggie ends I accumulate in the freezer for stock, so I didn't really measure my liquids. I also cut off any fatty pieces of meat and cooked them separately in the veggie stock pot so I could get the flavor but pour off the grease before adding to the stew - and not have any gristle in the stew. I Never would have discarded the vegetables as mentioned except so many reviews said it was worth doing. Yes indeed! Instead of mush, this was a very flavorful stew with nice texture - tender meat, thick gravy, and perfectly done potatoes and carrots. (Since I skipped the onion, I gave the veggie mush goodness to the dogs instead of tossing it out. They were very happy.) I am saving this recipe for my standard stew recipe.

