Rating: 4
My family loved this stew and my husband would like to try it made with buffalo in the future. Of course I used salt; it was called for in the recipe. This recipe will replace my old one. Instead of the oven, I made mine in a slow cooker which worked very well. I discarded nothing as that was unnecessary using the slow cooker. The first round of vegetables did not taste "cooked out". I added the main veg about half way through the cooking. When the meat was very tender, I found that the liquid needed some thickening so I sucked about half of it out of the crock with a baster, thickened it with a bit of corn starch in a small saucepan on the stove, and then mixed it back into the stew before serving it. Arrowroot would work too I suppose. Old vine zinfandel worked well for the wine. I think that browning the vegetables was indeed the special touch that gave this stew that deep, umami-enriched flavor. I used bacon fat, instead of olive oil, for browning btw and that also helped.

