To mdexter1: The problem, as A Cook from Louisville notes, is that, aside from salting the beef, the recipe calls for no salt. Salting generously while braising will give excellent results both immediately and the next day. Stewing the vegetables late in the process is a terrific idea, but 40 minutes for the carrots is still a little long; I wouldn't go longer than 20. But with these few adjustments, this is a fantastic winter stew.

